l - well up until I suppose they died - you know, with the different people he worked harder 'cos he knew everybody, and they used to say oh well, when Mr Andrew go round he'll pull them out the churchyard if he can find them and - to vote you know. He wo
r
ked for them all, all the Conservative people here. Mr Rosewarne used to come up and - you know, he had three or four cars and he - he used to - father would take - well he knew everywhere where to go and he would - all these old people would take notice 
of father and he - who must we vote for Mr Andrew? Oh, you vote for so and so, and they'd do it too. Whether it was a Parliamentary one or a parish one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Why do you think he held those views?
