\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 They had three b
oys. And then there was a one lived in Penzance. He married in Penzance, that was the youngest one. Then he went to Canada, the last I heard of him he was in Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you used to go to stay on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Mother perhaps used to take me down you know and - used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 On the train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, that's it, and then come down and fetch us. That would be a day out on each end, beginning and the end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 At home were friends invited into your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 How often, anytime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Oh yes, anytime they'd pop in. More so Sundays I think you know like the sort of weekends. And come down sometimes of an afternoon, go out for a walk with us. Yes, come and have a cup of tea and then - yes, that's it, yes, perhaps her husband'll be 
in the bed, you know, been on duty or something all night and - you know, what these young people are, well they - she didn't have any company, didn't know anybody in Pool, and she wasn't a good mixer you know. She was ever so nice - but she wasn't a good
 mixer you could tell that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Apart from Sundays any other particular days or occasions when friends would call?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh they'd call in anytime it seemed you know. Because - well for different things you know. 'Cos father was connected with so much and
 - mother used to get a bit fed up sometimes with them coming - you know, want their rates excused and - telling all - father all the - the story you know about their rates and - 'cos he was on that rating committee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That was with the parish council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Apart from the parish council what other things was he connected with, the parish council and the Bsset?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Institute. Conservative Association.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you say he was on the Board of Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, for years. On that rating
 committee, on the relief committee, on - well various committees you know, and he was a school governor as well, well they used to be called managers then, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 The Illogan schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. He - used to go across you know check up regist
ers. And Mrs Dot. Tremaine used to go with him, they used to go to Carnkie you know when they took their - well - minor scholarship it was then, he used to go with Mrs Maine, Mrs Dot Maine, he used to walk up to Fourlanes to sit all day to watch these chi
ldren that were taking their exams you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Was this before 1918 or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That must have been after '18, 1918, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 But he would have been on the Board of Guardians before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. I remember him as a - well I was going to say a little girl, going off to that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Where did he go for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Redruth Work House. That was the workhouse in Barncoose hospital.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 How often would he have to go off to these meetings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Once a fortnight, Friday m
ornings that used to be, he used to be in there all day then. And that was after he retired of course, that would be. Because he would go off all day. Now these meetings are like - you know, for the parish council, that would be evening meetings. And then
 
sometimes he's gone off in the afternoon, you know, to different - on different things, you know, when they used to go round for buildings and - seeing into things and - of course schools I think kept him going quite a bit too, going from one school to an
other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would Brancoose school come into his range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Brancoose, Carnkie, Illogan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would you remember him saying anything about the children from the Barncoose work house attending Barncoose school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well they used - oh yes, and 
they used to come here when I was going to school they used to come here and - come out in their brown corduroy - suits you know, and heavy hob boots. And walk -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did they all wear the same suits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Brown corduroy. And these poor boys used to 
walk you know over that main road - summertime, oh I've seen them come in school - with the sweat pouring out of them. They used to walk home to dinner too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No lighter wear for summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No. These great - heavy corduroy trousers, of course they were short trousers then, and these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 corduroy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
 jackets. And these girls used to dress up in heavy - heavy clothes, navy I think they were dressed in. And these poor girls used to be - you know, with other children with lighter clothes on, and they used to 
walk from Barncoose, out here in the mornings, back to dinner and out again in the afternoons. Yes, easy. And they used to walk in all the head and everything. Yes. Cart out here to school. They had hard going you know those - children did then. And of co
urse I suppose the food wasn't all that - good either that they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 So father was actually on the Board of Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would he have to do with the administration of the work house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well, yes, yes, yes, the workings. That's right,
 yes. Yes, he used to - Mrs Mr and Mrs Dunstan was the - masters. Yes, that - that's right. He was ever so nice there I believe you know, I've heard them say, yes. Yes. As far as they could go, because - of course, I suppose everything was tied then, and 
wasn't - that's it, yes, and it was a work house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did the children have to do any work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Oh yes, I believe they had to do a lot to help there as well. These bigger girls you know. And I believe some of them are a rough type you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Domestic work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. And unwanted children like I think a lot of them were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What would the boys have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh I think they had to do a lot of gardening and all, you know, there and - heavy work like I suppose chopping up firewood and all th
at sort of thing. Well I think they had a rough - rough gong you know the boys did in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 These children at school, did they mix in or did the other children sort of look down on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - I don't know, we didn't - it wasn't the same,
 you know, they were sort of - they used to keep themselves to themselves, you know, I know we used to mix and - all like that but I can remember them - in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 It was more embarrassment than anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes. Yes. I see lots of the families going 
round now, these here girls you know and they're - done quite well and - got nice little families and their children all grown up nicely. There's a lot of them around now I see them and remember them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did your parents friends call in casually without invitations sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, can you remember your parents when they got together with friends or neighbours, entertaining or making amusements in any kind of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well they just used to have a chat because there wasn't a lot of time for entertaining because - everybody had their homes and families to look after and it was - sort of an hour or two - and - you know, sort of gone again. Unless people c
ame from a distance, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And then they would just chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Talk about the all - that's right, the ordinary things going on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Ever play any games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. Not ordinary, not more than Christmas or - anything, no, no. Well, people us
ed to come one time - there was some - servants in Trevenson House there, when Mr Bain was there, and - they used to, you know, always say - always come up home and have a game of cards you know, 'cos they used to - they used to have whist drives then in 
a
id of the church - if they had - like they used to have so many hours off, they used to slip up with mother. And - oh we'll have a game of cards this evening, sometimes I had to be - pulled in to make the four. Oh, I used to hate playing cards, and mother
 
didn't mind at all. And my brother used to play. And if they were - you know, there was one missing they'd pull me in. Oh, I used to hate it, I couldn't see anything in it. They were good at it. These girls, they spent a lot of time, they were - well one 
was a chamber maid, one was - a nurse - nurse Fletcher she was, and she married Tiddy from Redruth, remember? You know, the Tiddy keep the boot shop there down in Chapel - that's right, he was a great bowler wasn't he. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 He would be their son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
That's right, yes. Well - their mother was a nurse - she - well she nursed the two Bain children you know, she was Nurse Fletcher, and I remember her coming - all of them coming to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 church}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373  you know in uniform and everything, and - they - they used - when they had time off they used to come up mother's too, 'cos father}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
knew them all see and of course father would get friendly and say look, well - if you'll only come on our place a bit, and then mother would get another two or three tacked on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 They were glad to have somewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, they were, yes. And they were nice girls you know, very respectable and nice mannered and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would your neighbours tend to call in casually at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 I had an uncle living next door, and his wife and family. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That's your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Yes, that's right, yes, they used to live next door, that was my father's brother, and their family, they had - oh they had five of them, and they used to be always coming to and for you know and we going in there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Apart from family would neighbours call in like casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And you would on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, of course there was only about three houses then in the road, when we went there to live, that little bungalow was built just aft
er we got there. And then the other four houses built after that. So that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 So there wasn't a very big community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh no, I can remember - you know, quite a number living there - then you know. Of course gone now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Many people divide society 
into different classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class or group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well yes, we did, there were some that we sort of looked up to you know, we thought well, we - we thought in 
those days that they were gentry you know like we had to be specially - prepared for those people - when they came round, and Mrs John Bain used to pop in - a lot - quite - well, I don't say a lot but she didn't mind at all going up and down and she'd com
e in and have - fun with my father you know, 'cos he was - a bit on the comical line, and she used to love - to come in and have a bit of chat with him and have a bit of fun. She was that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 This would be when she was out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, that's
 right, just out - perhaps out for a walk with the children if the nurse had a - afternoon off, she would take the children out for a walk, and - she used to pop in. She was ever so nice. She was - she was - well I don't know what, you wouldn't take any n
otice, you knew she was someone different to you, you know, better than you were, 'cos of course they had plenty of money and plenty of servants there then. Don't know what they'd say now if they came back to Trevenson House.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 But friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes, very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Can you think of anybody else, these were what you'd call the top classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
And Mrs - and Mrs Mayne used to come, Doctor Mayne's wife, where Miss Boot used to - I know - I remember my mother and father went out - when they had a car, they were the first ones in Pool to have a car.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Doctor Mayne?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Yes. And I always remember him taking mother and father to Lands End - one Sunday afternoon. 'Cos Mrs Mayne used to look up to my father, she was a governor of the school as wel
l, and - she would always wait - she'd say to father, now look, you tell me Mr Andrew what to vote for, she - well I don't know, she wasn't - I suppose not the right one for the job you know, and she would do everything that father done, and - she was alw
a
ys - you know, appreciated everything and - one Sunday afternoon they came and took mother and father out for a ride. So - they went to Lands End, in a little fawn - well - you know - with a hood on top you know, open top, yes, I always remember them comi
n
g picking - mother and father up that Sunday afternoon and we were thrilled to think they went too - you know, Lands End with Mr and Mrs - Doctor and Mrs Mayne. 'Cos they were like - people that we looked up to in Pool, 'cos she was kind and so - well Doc
tor as well you know. It is funny those things you - sort of remember always about those people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 He was the only doctor in Pool then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, he was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Can you think of anybody else in the Illogan area that you would consider to be in a higher class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Oh - see there was - of course Teague's have gone from there before I can remember. Then there was Captain Paull and Mrs - Mrs Paull used to call, and if there was sickness at all - she'd always make - sort of port wine jelly and that and b
ring up, you know, if there was anybody sick, and bring up fruit and - mother was poorly at any time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 They lived at Trevenson House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Trevenson, they went there - after the Bain's went, yes, that's it, yes. Yes. Clarence Paull's - mother
 and father. They were always very kind and - very good too. You know, coming in, Mrs Paull was. I don't remember - anyone else coming, more than, you know, anybody like from the church, the curates and the rectors always used to - come up to father for -
 to see what things were like when they were - coming here to Pool to live or - at Illogan anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What class would you consider them in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - well I suppose someone like you say - years ago the schoolmaster and the parson - they were the 
ideal people of the village weren't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would you class them with the Bains and the Maynes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - I don't know, I - no, I don't suppose you would really would you? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would you consider just slightly lower?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What class would you say you belonged to yourself then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
I - I couldn't - mongrels. Well I suppose - a sort of middle class could be couldn't it. I wouldn't say that we were on the poor line, we never knew any want of anything you know, we always - had a plenty of everything. Never threw away anything. But -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would you consider like a trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 s class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well yes, yes, if that is a class, yes. A working class anyhow. That's it, yes. Yes, I should say that. You know, working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Can you think of any other group that would come into that same kind of category?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Carpenters, shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, I suppose, yes. Yes. Yes, anybody like that would come in wouldn't they Like railwaymen or anything like that. You know. A w
orking -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 People with sound jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Making a decent livelihood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well we were alw
ays taught to respect everybody you know and - you know, mother used to say, now look, so and so might be here today, now mind you behave yourself and speak properly. And mind what you're saying. So - we were always - taught that way you know. To respect,
 that's right. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Were you ever told to curtsey to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Was your brother told to touch his cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, they had to do that in those days, and I remember when Alan started in the grammar school - we'd been i
n perhaps Redruth or Camborne or anywhere and he'd say, oh - here's Mr so and so coming, I'm going to turn my back granny, I'm not - I - I don't want to touch my cap, you know. He didn't like the idea of doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Can you remember who you would be told to curtsey to or show respect to in any special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - like these people that I just mentioned, you know, that - used to come occasionally to the door you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Was there anyone that you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well yes. A good many of those people that I've mentioned always - well everybody that I know of all showed respect - to them you know in every way when they - if there was an
ything necessary or wanted, and they were very thankful for all that father done for them. 'Cos he done a lot really during the wars and - well ordinary times going on because he was in that capacity of - you know, with being on the - Board of Guardians a
nd that sort of thing, 'cos everybody then wanted help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 If they wanted official guidance they would come to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, well they - yes, they used to come to him and he would tell them where to go if - he couldn't do anything for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would you consider he would have been considered one of the important people of the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well, he done a lot in Pool you know, I wouldn't like to say that - importance but done his duty like for all he came in contact with, or whatever he could do he'd do for them. And I don't think he complained, nothing was too much for him to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 His service to the community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Was of the highest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 These other folk that you mentioned, you did come in contact with them through your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Could you put into words why you consider they would have been considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well they had a better position I suppose than what - we were - or what my father was in you know so
rt - of professional then, and - I suppose that's why we looked up to them because we knew they were somebody - better perhaps than us. And in those days more money going through their hands. I suppose that's why we thought about - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Position and money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And property?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That's right, yes, in those days that's what you thought of didn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Shopkeepers, who would you consider they would associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well they were always nice to everybody if they w
anted - you know, 'cos - in those days there was - wasn't - more than a couple of shops in Pool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 They would be small shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, they would have, yes, no supermarkets then you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you know anything of the shopkeepers in Camborne or Redruth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Oh yes. OH - always done our shopping in Pool. Mr Willoughby the butcher. William Willoughby and - well the Willoughby's - grocers shop that's on the corner there. Miss Jolly I know - I - she used to be there. And Miss - Mrs Willoughby, at tim
es. And there was a Mrs Nancarrow there, she was there for many years too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 General store was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You said you thought that the clergy and the teachers were roughly on a par, what about farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well we looked -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Who would you consider they were on a par with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well - I suppose they were - I don't know, we didn't - of course they were all - sort - the farmers in those days were like on - hard working type weren't they and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Small farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 They were, yes.
 Yes, they were. And not like - well I suppose there are a lot of gentlemen farmers now, because - in those days they had to work hard on farms didn't they. There was nothing - sort of mechanical like there is now. To be used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Like Mr Hosken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh - I know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 There weren't any big scale farmers around here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Not like the Penna's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No, no, they were - well they used to live over to - of course he lives up here now, Mr Penna does.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Any other employers did you know in your locality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Mr Willoughby - well the Willoughby's had the - the - both shops, the grocers shop and the butchers shop, though they were two brothers weren't they then. I think that's the family that were there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 The other employers would have been the factory owners and that outside of the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You wouldn't have come across them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Nor know anything about their social life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What sort of people would you say went to church as opposed to chapel, was there any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well I believe we did have a - better class people in those days going to church, people that we could look up to. Now, such as Patience Basset, she was confirmed down here, and whatever was wanted in the
 church they'd always go to the Bassets for it. Because of course they built that church there. And they provided all the Frontals and - all this - that sort of thing, you know, for the - Bassets of Tehidy, so that we - sort of - we always had someone - w
e
 was never - I was going to say we always had somewhere where we could go for money, you know - if it was - wanted. But now we haven't anybody like that to look to, people with plenty of money that say well - here's five pounds, go and spend it or - towar
ds anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 The Bassets had the living of that church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. That's right, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What about the chapel, what sort of people would you say went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - the business people I suppose in Pool, well the Willoughby's
 used to go there, they were the mainstay I think of - such as Pool Wesley. And - I think they were the main - that was the main chapel then, you know, those days, I don't think St Martins had anybody like that. But - Pool Wesley I think was the Willoughb
y's was - their - saving grace there because - they had money, in business with butchers shops and - Harry Willoughby and his father. So that - Well see that Kenneth Kendal is a nephew - to - George Willoughby that used to live up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Where you lived
 here in Pool did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were differences within the working class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well all around where we lived they were all the same, you know, all - for living and - that sor
t of thing. But all the families in those days you know they all used - used to go off to chapel and - all the families used to go in those days, all the - and they were big families then too. I can remember you know looking up from - where we used to liv
e
 over to Pumpfield Row - well they used to always go as families to chapel then, and then they were big families, five or six children - used to see trotting off, and sometimes more. See them coming in from Sunday school all with their white outfits on - 
in summertime and - so that's how they lived I think, you know, mostly that was their - all - all their outings really. They didn't look to go very far a field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did they mostly earn their living by -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh I think it was mining. You know, in the mines. Yes, I think so and working on - top - on the surface you know, different things.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 There were several big mines here then weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes, there were, Tincroft, South Corfty, East Pool and - well I suppose lots of them used to work outs
ide on the mines 'cos there wasn't a lot of factories. You see, Climax was the only - well Stephens the Foundry it used to be then. That was the only - the biggest place here I suppose and Electric Works was nothing very much then - in those days. They di
dn't employ a lot of people I don't expect. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 The gas works only came - did you remember gas coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Yes. Oh I don't know about coming, I remember seeing those things you know down Tuckingmill there, all those - gas works there. But I don't remember - not - any gas being around in the houses then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Do you think that any one group felt themselves superior to the rest in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - like it is now. How come - think more of themselves than other people think of them. They t
ry to think they're one above - I think. Just like it is now with - families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 It's a question of self-esteem I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes. Yes. I can look back now and 
I've even said you know when I've been talking - now to the children here sometimes - and they'd said about this one, oh I said, I can remember them years ago, what they were like, you know, and - oh the roughest of the rough. Living in Pumpfield Row ther
e, because that was a little place now - it has got more or less respectable now, people are buying houses and modernizing them and all, but all the - the poorer class always used to live up there you know and - those three rows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Those terraced cottages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
That's it, yes. Yes, some - a lot living - there was three rows then, well then they - as the years gone on they've knocked them through and made them into one house - so as there's two - that's it, yes. And you wonder at families in two rooms. An
d five or six children. You wonder how they managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Do you remember any distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - no, I don't think so or we were never brought to - sort of look down on anybody because - they weren't tradesmen or anyt
hing like that. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Your parents would have the same attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Oh yes, I think so, yes. Well whether they were poor or what happened, or - you know, what - position they were in in life. We sort of never looked down on anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You were saying about these rough people in the Rows, did you ever remember any children going to school without shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well, no, I - well - shoes - pretty well - out on the ground you know or - their feet on the ground yes. Yes. Yes, some of them I can rem
ember now looking awful you know with their - streaming wet feet and - and - oh all the leather gone from the bottoms and - so - of course I suppose in those days there was a need of it in some cases - for people because they didn't have the money to buy 
t
heir shoes, see the wages that they were getting and what they had to do with it - but - I know there was no canteens or anything like that in schools then, and not electric light. I remember them over there you know the - these old souls that used to cle
a
n the school, when we were coming out they were going over there with their brushes and dusters carrying and - waiting for the children to go out and - she used to be over in the mornings half past six lighting the fires to - and all grate fires then in t
h
e rooms, and she'd be over there with a candle going round from one room to another lighting. Well now, in the sunshine they keep the lights on there in the front, where they could put them off and economise, but - when it is lovely with summertime and su
nshine they've got - and the sun coming in and they've got all those lights on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to any particular social class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No, she always kept herself respectable, she thought - you know, that - we
ll I don't say that she was it or anything like that but she sort of - always kept her head above water you know, kept herself - very respectable in that way. I mean for dress and - oh she mixed with and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would this be as she was brought up in her own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well, yes, I suppose it was, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Was it possible at that time do you think to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well I don't know - I don't think it was - so - wouldn't be so easy then as what it is now because everybody seems 
to be one equal almost now don't they, 'cos they're all getting plenty of money and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That's right, education you see is being brought out in - youngsters isn't it. They've got the opportunity now if there's brains there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And nobody is that poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You can't remember any special one who did move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well like those people that I've refe
rred to now, you know, that we knew that that they were in a good position. We - we sort of looked up to them and thought they were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And that would be because of their position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, that's right, yes. Yes. And of course there were other nice people around you know that we sort of respected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 A real lady in the personal sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Yes. If anybody - you know, we felt that was - dirty and - dishonest, you know, we - sort of - well felt we were better than them, I suppose that's what - how you would put it, 'cos we were always brought up that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Do you remember seeing a policeman around, well of course you lived near the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, they were on the - on beat all the time going up and down the road and we kn
ew them all - to talk to and - mix with, but now you don't know them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 How do you think they treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh, they were grand. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did your parents ever say if you were naughty I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - yes, I believe 
they did, all right, I'll tell - although we weren't afraid of the policemen because we were friendly with them all. 'Cos they used to talk to us you know. So that we did - weren't afraid. Not like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Your home here in Church Road your father had built, your previous home was that rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you see anything of the landlord then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. I don't know who those houses belonged to. And I've heard them say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You don't know anything about the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Whether he was good as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No, no - 'cos we were - well I don't remember being there very long. We were there as little ones. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. I never - you
 know, father was always - and he - he - I know he invested money in shares and that and he always done very well with them - in - Shipping shares and all like that, Mr Uren - up there, he used to do a lot of it - Edwin Uren, he was the shoemaker as well 
u
p there, and he used always to advise father, I can look back over it now although I didn't know what he was doing, but I always remember him saying you know and then if he sold them he always done well - always remember seeing these things around Hain's 
S
hipping - Shares, you know, and whatever he - put - sort of put his money he did - sort of didn't lose you know that's why - he kept his ends up I suppose like he did. So that we never knew the shortage of - anything you know, we - had no struggle at all.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Was father ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you know anyone who ever go help from the Guardians, or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. Several people - I know around, and even now - there's a person living on Illogan Highway, she alw
ays says to me, oh I shall never forget your father, he was good as gold to me. And I was living up so and so and didn't matter when I came down - your mother would always say, come in and sit down, you've walked a long way. And I always had every help wi
th your father and I knew he would do his best for me you know. She always say that to me now and she's an old woman now. And different ones, you know, not - that isn't the only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 So the Guardians here treated the people reasonably well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh ye
s. Yes. And father didn't forget to tell them if - there was anything passed in there and - they've gone to these people that should have had something if they didn't have it he'd go up to them and give them beans. He'd say, you're supposed to do this and
 
you're supposed to do that and you haven't done it. So you must do it. Well it was done then I think against - they didn't want to you know sometimes. But he'd see it was done. Same as the rates. Yes. Same for rates, if - people have - come to him and sai
d
 you know they couldn't do this or couldn't do that, all right, he said, you leave it all to me Missus, you give me your papers and I'll see it's done, and he would see, oh and they would come down - oh - so grateful to you Mr Andrew for what you done for
 me and - well that was a - compliment to him wasn't it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it? Do you remember ahhone being made to leave by rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Durmmed out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No, no, I don't think so 'cos there was no wireless in those days. Nothing like that you know. No. No. Not vandalism like it is now.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Were you given lessons by either of your parents or any tutors before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Three. Three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh nine o'clock. We had to put in the full day I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh we were out about half past three then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You went all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh it would be infants school. Across the road you know, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 County education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, that's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh - not living very far off - two minutes from home I was in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 I remember mother taking us to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Home. Going back - going home then, there was no canteens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What did you think of school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh lovely. No trouble at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Yes. I've got photographs now of when we were in the infants school - with Miss Prisk, and Mrs Hart was it, she was Miss Uren - Godfrey Uren's sister, remember her? Lived in Camborne.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you like the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Oh yes. Yes, grand. Miss Prisk was a bit strict, she used to put a look on us you know, like this, and we knew that was enough when she done that you know to us. But we were happy little school as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you always go to Pool school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes, I didn't go - didn't go anywhere else, I wouldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Right through to fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That's it, yes. And - they wanted me - when Mr Jopling was here then, and Mr Jago and they w
ere always coming up to mother and father for me to - study harder to go - take a scholarship you know, and I was supposed to go to Camborne the Saturday mornings we used to have to go you know, and I wouldn't go. And I didn't go. Oh they were wild with m
e after when I went back the Monday morning to school. Laura Jago took the - we were like three of us about the same age and we were supposed to take it that day and they went and got through and I didn't go, I didn't want to. No ambition at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did your brother take the entrance exam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Yes, he got through all right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And he went to the grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Well he - well - of course he - he must have gone there just after it was opened I suppose. Redruth. Because he'
s seventy - seventy-six is it this year. I'm seventy-four this year and he's - a year a nine months older than me, seventy-six in August. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did the teachers emphasis certain things as important in life, for example manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What about tidiness?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Were they strict on ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Not all that much I don't think, no, not like they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes, we had to be in school and - not allowed out - not - you know until
 - the certain, not like they are now, trailing around and going in there at any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh well we were punished, had to do words then, hundred words or five hundred words you kn
ow and if it was very drastic it was a thousand words. We had to stay in after school and do it, or stay in playtime. Of course that was a great punishment then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That was the only way you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. We never had the cane I don't think. I got pretty near to it lots of times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 They did sometimes punish children with the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Yes. Yes. Mr Jago used to say to me, he was the headmaster and he said, oh - you'll be ashamed to look at me when I'm old and grey, he said, when I see you you'll be ashamed to look at me. I always think about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Were the girls punished in the same way as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Boys sometimes - we used to get - you know we had a - quite a rough lot there, used to come from the Rows in Tucking mill 
you know and - Roscroggan and and all those - you know, they were quite a poor rough lot, and they used to get punished and the work house boys, you know, they had to be very strict with them. And then did -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What sort of offences were they punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well - I don't know, they must have - for fighting, they used to do a lot of fighting these boys did, some of them were very rough. And they were punished they used to have the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did they gang up according to the areas where they came from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No, I don't think so, but I think the - these work house boys all stuck together you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You don't remember any gangs or groups in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No, no. No. No, nothing of that then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well, sometimes you used to feel sorry for them, you know, they used to be left out because - they couldn't dress like some of the others could, and they did look down and out and poor. And weren't clothed or fed I don't think like some where 
and of course they - didn't come up to the standard in lots of things. For what they were wanted for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 In what way, were they sort of tired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - the - their manners for one thing - and they way they - you know, their appearance - was very poor, and they looked poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Untidy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes. And their heads, you know, some of them, the way they used to do their - you know, oh some of their heads used to be awful.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Couldn't have a proper hair cut?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No. No. And the girls, some of 
- you know, the long hair then. I remember now sitting beside of them you know. Mother used to be very - terrified if I came home and she saw anything you know. Oh yes, give it a good brushing every night and small toothcombs were used then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did the school nurse come and look at heads then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, just roughly you know not - nothing very - much then. Just occasionally they used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes. Yes. They were always - yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did they ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That's it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
My father did, see he used to go in to count the children you know like they used to do then in those days. I don't know whether they do it now or not. Of course they were school managers then. Now they're governors aren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Your father met the teachers of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes, oh yes, he knew them all. And I think that's how we got off so well at - with the teachers as we did, when we were going to scho
ol because knowing father was coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Not all the children came from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh no. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well I think so some - sometimes
 we could see it you know. I know I took up for my cousin one day, he was in the same class as me, he lives up the road now. He always say about it, we had a pupil teacher there, and he was always o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 n him. He was a Pe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 naluna from Cam borne, and there was a M
r Napp and Penaluna came as pupil teachers. And he was forever on him, and I said to him one day, he came in, and - he - started on - Arthur again, he was Arthur Andrew too, was funny, and so I said to him, I said, you're always on him like that I said, w
h
at are you on him like that for all the time, I said, you're always picking on him if there's anybody to pick on. De said, you keep quiet. I said, I shant. He said, you'll go outside the room. I said, I shan't. I said, and I - so - well - they - lots have
 said to me since, I always remember you speaking out like that, because in those days you - you were sort of afraid, but he was only a young chap see, just on - you know school practice or pupil teaching. And I always used to think when I saw him after.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Why should he have been on your cousin do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well I don't know, whether he wasn't very bright or not, you know, and - didn't want to learn like - was sort of more playful perhaps you know. No patience. And I suppose he thought he wasn't go
ing to waste time on him, I spoke up for him. And then he was sort of quite - he wouldn't answer anybody back you know so I - spoke up for him. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Fourteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 I suppose I should have had to - in those days, you know, you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Not from choice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you do any part time education after?
