\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 A sort of popping sound?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
You were saying that the house that you lived in in those days like all the other houses here, there weren't any bathrooms. Most of them had toilets away up the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Was yours like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No. Ou
rs led right out through the scullery - a little place all to itself you know but we could go - indoors, we - didn't have to go out - for it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 When you said that the clothes during the first war were brought down here for distribution by various p
eople like the Guardians, where did they mean in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well from the - parish vestry - they were distributed I think, you know, people had forms sent out - to fill in - as to what they wanted, and then they could go there and - perhaps someone
 would go there perhaps - you know, an hour or two beforehand and make up the parcel for Mrs so and so. If she wanted vests, nightdresses or - underwear, or anything like - or boots or shoes they would do what they could and put them in the parcel and she
'
d come at a certain time and collect them. 'Cos there were - forms made - you know, sent - or these people had them when they came - to ask for something, these forms would be given them - and of course they would fill them out as to what they wanted and 
by the time they come to collect them, they were ready for them. And that was done in the parish vestry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Were the forms is}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 ued by the Board of Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No, the Relief Committee, yes, that's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Was the parish vestry attached to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
No, not the church. The Rate Room. You know, it belonged to the council really, was a council - place there where we pay our rates. This was a room allocated upstairs for us. And I can remember seeing that room full of clothing you know
 that come down. Was sent from various places, it was - you know, quite good clothing. New some of it. Most of it was new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What would the parish vestry be used for apart from that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well they used to use it for meetings then, their parish meetin
gs. You know, like the parish council that was before Redruth and Camborne amalgamated with Illogan, they used to have the Illogan Parish Council meetings there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Your father was on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. And that was always in the upstairs room. Over the Rate Room and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 The rates were paid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Would there be any meetings concerning the rates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes. Rates Excusal meetings and all that sort of thing was handled there. That was the only place they had to - use you know, when
 it was - the parish council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 The Illogan Parish Council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 And at Trevenson the parish vestry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You spoke of the Bain family and their servants being quite friendly and neighbourly and mixing with the village around,
 can you remember anything of the Bassets being friendly, or their servants coming around to church or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
No, I used to see them coming to church in their - black Maria, going to Illogan church and of course all the - all the seats were all - all pane}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 led off then, they had their seats - you couldn't see the servants, Mr Basset would sit in the - well they had a place as big as this with lovely comfortable chairs around. And then there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373  all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
cord - well not cordoned off, it was all woodwork
, all oak panels - put back a long way and doors put in so as the servants could sit in behind them. Well you couldn't see them more than when they stand up during the hymns or anything. But Mr and Mrs Basset would be sitting in a - sort of a circular pla
c
e. In Illogan church that would be, yes. In church. They had a place all set aside, now - the alter that's in - Illogan parish church now - is - made of those panels that came out those doors you know, where the servants used to go in and sit, and part of
 
where their - they had half of the - one of the aisles was - specially - purposed - done off for them. For the Basset family, and they always used to sit in there on their own. And of course when they came they were dressed as servants, you know, you knew
 
that they were something different, but they used to come up - I - you know, sort of picture them now coming up - we used to call it the Black Maria's come today, and out they used to come and - the Bassets, they used to come on ahead you know in a cab or
 - landau or something like that. And the servants used to come on in this other one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 A sort of covered wagon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
drawn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 That's right, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What sort of uniform would distinguish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh - well they would -
 have - you know, little - sort of little - I can remember them black straw hats, you know, on - on top and just navy coats. There was nothing - nothing - no dress up with them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No Sunday best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did they ever come to Trevenson church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Yes. Patience Basset was confirmed at Trevenson church when I was. And I remember, of course we had to go in alphabetical order, but - of course I was A and she was B buy she went before me. I had to give in, she was done before - me. 
She was B you see and I was A, well that was that. So I always remember sitting nearby me and I've watched her dress, she had a - beautiful white silk dress on, she was very fair. I - should think she could be another - colouring, you know, like Princess 
A
nne, she looked like, you know, that sort of girl, she was - sort of heavily built girl, and I always remember watching all she had on you know, 'cos she sat beside of me, but she wasn't prepared for confirmation not with us. But I can remember her coming
 to Trevenson, but not the others. Always remember the others went to Illogan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 She would have confirmation classes privately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 I suppose she had private I expect, yes, I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Where did you have yours then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 We had ours at the church y
ou know, and sometimes we went to the church house, in Poole, where the - curate lived then. Yes. 'Cos the rector was always at Illogan you see, so the curate was left here on his own to - do that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Do you remember what the dress was like that Miss Basset?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
It was a nice white silk, and made beautiful you know, of course there was something different about it to what ours was. And white - of course white shoes and stockings then as well. She was nice - a nice looking, fair girl, very fair, her bro
ther was darker, Ronnie Basset. I went to Illogan when he dedicated the new altar there, with the wood that came out of his father's - their father's pews. They remember - I remember Mrs Basset singing at Illogan too. Mr Basset's wife. She was a Trelawney
,
 and I remember her singing there. I remember her singing with a chap called - Argballl I think he was called, she sang - come let us join our cheerful songs. I always remember her taking part, this other one he had - she had a lovely voice, beautiful voi
ce. She only sang on special occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Trelawney where from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 The Trelawney's from - what - Bodmin they had a seat didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you all wear white at the confirmation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, we wouldn't do any other than that in th
ose days. Now they - don't study that sort of thing I don't think. I've seen 'em all in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11157569\charrsid12073373  - well not vivid colours, grey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
 and navies and - some whites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Can you remember any other happenings that involved the local people with the Bassets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well all 
the - I don't know why or - how they got entitled to - to get this beef at Christmas from Tehidy, but they used to pass - walking down, you know, I've seen them coming up -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 What sort of people would you think would get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - very poor peopl
e and probably out of work people or something like that, because - they used to come up with their - they used to carry I should think a towel with them, a white towel or something like that, and all their meat would be - sort of they'd be carrying it ri
ght out without a basket or anything just their little white packages you know of beef, for Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 They'd go in to Tehidy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Tehidy for them, walk to Tehidy, there was no transport to take the, they had to walk - to get it. And then I remember 
- the tea treats. Mr Basset used to give all the school children in the parish - a free treat every year, and I remember from this school - walking down to Tehidy, we had a - fife and drum band, the boys brigade beyd - to head us. Oh, that was the day of 
o
ur lives to go to Tehidy, and when we - were going down the drive like - where the golf links is now we should see Illogan school coming across here, they had a band as well heading them. And then Carnkie school or all those schools used to come on, Barnc
o
ose - used to come on, and we all used to walk to Tehidy, with this band, and that was the day of our lives, with all our cups and all and then - when we got to Tehidy we used to go in the big field, before you come to the golf links or the hos - of cours
e
 it was their house then, and - in the field - there would be - oh huge troughs of goats milk, that would be our drink there. And we'd go with our cups and take out the goats milk and drink - whenever we wanted it. There was big troughs there with it, and
 - then -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Wooden troughs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
No, it was sort of - galvanized troughs there, and then - there was a sort of a - oh I suppose it could be a small lawn, and there was a sort of a drain going there, I suppose it was to drain the water from the field wh
ere we was, and they would stand across on this - lawn, and - it was sort of higher up than the field, and they would have tins of - tinned sweets, you know, he - sticky sweets, loads of them, and they would throw them all over to us, and we'd pick them u
p
 from the grass and eat them, fighting, you know to - to - pick up all those - the - sweets from the grass. Didn't matter what was in the grass or anything, they'd all go. And they used to throw away tins of them there. Then we used to have tea treat buns
 and everything given to us there. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Who would throw the sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Well - somebody belonging to the Bassets used to come out and do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Yes. They were sort of - and I suppose the workmen there because you see it was full -
 of - servants there, staff and - all and we used to have a grand time there. And these sweets, I can see them now, with these great - you know, tins of - tinned sweets. And you know they'd stick to the grass too. And we - used to take them up and eat the
m and enjoy them. Now of course we should be poisoned I suppose if we done such a thing. And this goats milk, I can see these big troughs of goats milk. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Did you have games and things there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh yes, games were all organised and - there was a
 part of the - beside the house that we could go up and have a look around. 'Course they had to watch or else people - they were watching all the time, and I always remember going up - and there was little cemeteries there - in the grounds, little headsto
n
es you know for the dogs and - all the little things that had died, their pets I suppose some of them, little small headstones, it was beside the house. We used to think that was lovely to go up there and look around, and then there was a big pond there, 
they had a pond, you know, with - swans in them. But we didn't - we weren't allowed to go very near that. Was beautiful right down in the front you know, the - where the hospital is now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 You didn't go near the pond?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 It was really a big lake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Oh it is there, yes, that's where the water I suppose - goes down to Bell Lake there. I suppose that's the pond that drains from there. - Course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No boating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 No, no. I don't know whether it's still there or not. In the front 
of the house. Of course you wouldn't know - the place now. To when we used to go there you know years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 All the different denominations would organise their own children to go?
