\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14353856 MP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 
Well - of course you always felt that - that the tradesmen was one above the labourers you know, I - I can remember now people coming in - you know, work - to work and - sort of labourers, well you didn't have m
uch to do with them, you know, you looked up to the tradesmen that was looking after you, and you knew who they were, or we did. But we thought the labourers were the - were labourers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13971602 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365183\charrsid12073373 There was a class distinction?
